1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:06,290
Each record in a partition receives a monotonically increasing integer called an offset, starting at 0.

2
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:09,730
Offsets uniquely identify a record within a partition.

3
00:00:09,730 --> 00:00:13,750
Consumers track their position by storing the last processed offset.

4
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:18,615
Real talk: I've seen senior engineers at Uber get this wrong in interviews.

5
00:00:18,615 --> 00:00:20,365
Don't be that person.

